To launch the web app

1) npm install

2) npm start

3) go to https://localhost:4430



User management app
  Simple user management web app making use of the MEAN stack and jade templates. 
  Data is accessed through an API available at /api/...
          GET /api/users <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></span> list users
      POST /api/users <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></span> add users
      GET /api/user/:name <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></span> user info (where :name is the unique username) (REQUIRES AUTH)
      DELETE /api/user/:name <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></span> delete user (where :name is the unique username) (REQUIRE AUTH)
      POST /api/auth <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></span> authenticate
  The app tries to access a mongo database located at localhost:27017. If you want to change this, modify <b> mongo/connect.js. </b>



Rules
  Everybody can view the current list of users.
  Everybody can add new users (name + email).
  The admin can log in the site to see user details and delete user. Admin account is created when the server starts
          Username is "admin"
      Password is "admin"
  Authentication is handled with a jsonwebtoken stored in local storage and given to the API in the authorization header. Token are valid for 24 hours.
